_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 384w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/415x277/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 415w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/480x320/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 480w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/540x360/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/640x427/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/750x500/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 750w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/828x552/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 828w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1080x720/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 1080w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1200x800/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 1200w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1440x960/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 1440w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/1920x1280/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 1920w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/2048x1365/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 2048w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/2400x1600/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/2400x1600/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408595/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0279.jpg"/></noscript></span></div></div></figure></div></div><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"><figcaption class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline text-gray-13 dark:text-gray-e9 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-black [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-e9 dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-13 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63"><em>Kenneth Lobo Méndez, director of planning and sustainability in electricity management at the state-run electricity utility Instituto Costarricense de Electricidad (ICE). </em>The Verge<em> spoke with Lobo Méndez at the Cachí dam in Costa Rica.</em></figcaption></div></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><strong>How is climate change affecting electricity generation?</strong></p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><strong>KLB:</strong> That’s a big challenge, how to manage the hydropower resource in the future. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Our own studies have shown that in the short term, we won’t see a significant impact. In the mid term, like in 2030, in the north of the country, there will be a decrease in rainfall. Most of the country’s hydropower capacity is in the north. So, it will be affected. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">In the long term, what we see is an increase in hydropower production — but in the west and south of the country, mainly because rains will get heavier, more intense in that region. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><strong>Marco Jiménez Chavez:</strong> There’s a hydroelectric plant called Arenal. It’s one of the most important plants in the country, and it’s in the zone where we expect lower precipitation due to climate change. In the south of the country, we will get heavier rainfall. However, we can’t get that rainfall into our system; our plants are not ready to harness that amount of water. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><strong>So how will you prepare for that?</strong></p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white"><strong>MJC:</strong> Diversify. </p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The thing with a renewable energy system is that you also need to diversify so that you won’t be subjected to only the availability of water. You can avoid that risk and share the risk with the other energy sources. Hydropower will still be a great percentage of the country’s energy mix, but new energy sources will be added to the system, for example: solar power and wind. Another important source is geothermal because it’s the only renewable energy source that does not depend on climate variability.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph mb-20 font-fkroman text-18 leading-160 -tracking-1 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">We’ve got a problem because hydropower does not have the same variability as solar wind. So, if we get more solar and more wind, our system will have more variability. So, we need to get back up to that variability. And that’s where batteries are also important.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component clear-both block md:float-left md:mr-30 md:w-[320px] lg:-ml-100"><div class="my-9 md:my-0"><div class="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"><div class="fixed inset-0 h-[110vh] w-full bg-white transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out z-[-1] cursor-default opacity-0" role="button" aria-label="Close" tabindex="0"></div><div role="button" aria-label="Zoom" tabindex="0" class="visible z-30 w-full origin-center transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out cursor-zoom-in"><figure class="transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out lg:mx-0"><div><div class="duet--media--content-warning relative" style="padding-top:66.66666666666666%"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="A smiling man stands in front of electric power lines." src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="A smiling man stands in front of electric power lines." loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" sizes="(max-width: 1023px) 100vw, 744px" srcSet="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/376x251/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408597/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0311.jpg 376w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/384x256/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408597/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0311.jpg 384w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/415x277/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408597/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0311.jpg 415w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/480x320/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408597/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0311.jpg 480w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/540x360/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408597/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0311.jpg 540w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2700x1800/640x427/filters:focal(1350x900:1351x901):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25408597/111023_Cachi_Dam_ICE_JCalma_0311.jpg 640w, https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumb